15,01  "14,15       15,01                  NewsLetter Issue #1
15,01    "14,15     
15,01      "14,15   
15,01        "14,15 
15,01  
15,01Introduction

15,01        Havok has been formed from two other groups, MiC and Prophecy,
15,01        the first coming out of the Chicago burbs, and the other from
15,01        Ontario Canada.  The first Havok Pack is looking pretty good,
15,01        it isn't huge, but we have learned to leave out the lower 
15,01        quality ansi's from past experience :)

15,01New Members:

15,01        Well since it's the first pack we are all new members, and the 
15,01        only member who joined and wasn't previously in either group is
15,01        the Replicant, and he's doing a great job.  

15,01Members resigning:

15,01        Polaris has resigned from our artwork division, something about
15,01        group wars :-) but he was too busy to produce much anyways.  
15,01        Tron also resigned from our artwork division, and he joined 
15,01        another group based in 7O8 called Visual Insanity, so good luck
15,01        to him there.  Spock also resigned from our Lit department 
15,01        towards the end of March, so he still has quite a bit of work
15,01        in the pack. 

15,01News

15,01        Well since we are a new group we obviously need some more 
15,01        artists/coders/members in general.  I am not sure at this
15,01        point whether there will be an application generator in 
15,01        the pack or not.  Personally i don't see the need for one
15,01        since all they do is take up space and you need to upload
15,01        samples of your work anyway, so if you want to apply then
15,01        upload  some of your work  (coding or art or whatever) to 
15,01        the Thieves' Guild 7O8-261-1849 or The Acropolis 7O8-557-
15,01        2826.

15,01Coding

15,01        Well in coding news we have had an interesting time, Bleys
15,01        who was supposed to write the viewer came down with a 1O2 
15,01        fever right before he left on vacation, so he couldn't 
15,01        finish it, but Lightning (independent) coder jumped in and
15,01        helped us out by coding a viewer in Q-Basic, and it was 
15,01        pretty good considering time constraints, but fortunately
15,01        Techie happened to be at my house, and i said "Think ya 
15,01        could code us a decent viewer in 2 days?", and he came up
15,01        with the best viewer i have ever seen.  It's a DOS command
15,01        line viewer with 25 line mode with scrollback up to 3800
15,01        lines or so, 640x480 mode, and 320x200 mode with scroll
15,01        back.  The viewer is also a HUGE 3k or was it 2k big.  In
15,01        other words, this thing kicks ass, it's WAY faster then 
15,01        ACiDView and it's also 1/60 the size, and has scroll back 
15,01        on 320x200 mode.  So unless you're a windows-need-a-menu
15,01        type guy, this will be the viewer of choice for you. 
15,01        
15,01Artwork: 

15,01        Well in the RiP department the Hitman is still our sole 
15,01        rip artist.  He's changed his style to make his work a 
15,01        little more shaded, but he's still one of the best in 
15,01        the biz in my opinion.
